Largest session yet. Started with biomimetic analysis, ended with
slot-scoped multi-ref one-to-many notes. Key deliverables:

1. COMPOST: decomposition for stale notes. --dry-run, --report,
   --compost, --renew flags. Per-OID and per-path targeting.
   Context stratification (stale one-liners, composted hidden).

2. SLOTS: multiple notes on same object via named producer slots.
   --slot flag on note/read/follow/compost. Context/doctor/find/
   kinds/prime aggregate all slots. Supersedes intra-slot only.
   OID ambiguity detection when multiple slots match.

3. AGENT-NATIVE (principle 9): every command works non-interactively.
   Interactive prompts are convenience, never the only path.

4. OVERWRITE WARNING: shows existing note kind+title before clobber.

5. PRIME: outputs skill + live repo state for agent onboarding.

6. DEVELOPMENT PRINCIPLES: added #8 (branch for features) and
   #9 (agent-native by default).

Meta: session was itself the test. Made every mistake the new
features now prevent — overwrote root tree without reading it,
forgot branching workflow, built human-only interactive loop.
Each failure became a tool fix or culture note.

Consulted gpt-5.4 (openai-codex via tmux pi instance) on the
one-to-many design. It recommended slot-scoped multi-ref with
ref-qualified attachment identities. Built and tested.

223 tests, 0 failures. 55 slot topology tests with ground-truth
git-state assertions verifying creation and composting persist.
